links.title: Genetx, Ultragenyx report serious adverse event for Angelman syndrome candidate (NASDAQ:RARE)
links.description: Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical (NASDAQ:RARE) and its collaborating partner , GeneTx Biotherapeutics, have reported interim data from the Phase 1/2 study evaluating GTX-102 in Angelman syndrome.Though according to the interim data from the first five patients treated indicate, substantial improvements in all patients in at least two disease domains including communication, behavior, sleep, gross motor function, and fine motor function as measured by the improvement scale at day 128.

Only thing interesting is that the price is of the stock bought is like $5/share 
 
Then what happens?  SLDB keeps working on bringing the drug to market.  If I owned, id sell some or all.  I wouldn't buy the stock. 
 
Time to bookmark this plan and see what happens over the next couple weeks
